I feel like I should chime in that zweihanders are a lot lighter and faster than games make them out to be. Most only ranging from 4-8 pounds. They're mainly made to be anti-pike weapons since they were invented to deal with pike formations. They also make great bodyguard weapons since using large sweeping motions with the sword's long reach gave you a lot of breathing room. Also the part between the hooks and actual guard is called a ricasso and wasn't sharpened so you could grab it like the an extension for the handle for certain techniques. And if you want something more visually striking look into flamberge zweihanders.
Landschneks were also quite fond of their pistols and rifles. Germany even had an entire horseback gunmen group called the black riders.
